Package: DEGASv2
Title: Deep Optimal Transport Framework for Disease Risk Heterogeneity
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ziyu", "Liu", role = "aut"),
    person("Travis", "Johnson", email = "johnstrs@iu.edu", role = "aut"),
    person("Sihong", "Li", email = "lisih@iu.edu", role = "aut"),
    person("Jiahui", "Liu", email = "jl370@iu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Jiahui Liu <jl370@iu.edu>
Description: Implements a deep optimal transport framework to model disease risk 
    heterogeneity across multiple disease contexts including prostate cancer, 
    Alzheimer's disease, and multiple myeloma. The package provides preprocessing 
    utilities, deep optimal transport analysis, and visualization tools for 
    identifying clinically meaningful molecular subtypes and treatment responses.
